      • checkPackages

        public static void checkPackages(SBMLDocument doc)
        Checks the whole SBMLDocument, including all siblings, to make sure that the package version and namespace is set properly.

        It will print warnings or errors when problems are found, nothing will be changed.

        Parameters:
        doc - the SBMLDocument to check.

      • checkPackages

        public static void checkPackages(SBMLDocument doc,
                                 boolean silent,
                                 boolean fix)
        Checks the whole SBMLDocument, including all siblings, to make sure that the package version and namespace is set properly.

        The given boolean parameters will indicate if the method will print warnings or errors when problems are found, and if it will try to fix problems.

        Parameters:
        doc - the SBMLDocument to check.
        silent - boolean to indicate if errors and warnings should be shown.
        fix - boolean to indicate if encountered problems should be fixed.

      • checkPackages

        public static void checkPackages(SBase sbase,
                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> packageNamespaces,
                                 boolean silent,
                                 boolean fix)
        Checks the given SBase, including all it's siblings, to make sure that the package version and namespace is set properly.

        The given boolean parameters will indicate if the method will print warnings or errors when problems are found, and if it will try to fix problems.

        Parameters:
        sbase - the SBase to check.
        packageNamespaces - the List of namespaces that are expected to be found SBML L3 packages.
        silent - boolean to indicate if errors and warnings should be shown.
        fix - boolean to indicate if encountered problems should be fixed.
